{
  "_comment": "Per-source actor rewrites applied BEFORE cross-document merging. Keys are source_document values (e.g. 'Japan25.pdf' or 'https://...'). Each rule has 'match' (case-insensitive regex on the full entity name) and either 'replace' (new name; supports $1/$2 capture groups), 'drop' (remove the actor + its edges), or 'drop_if_unmapped' (remove only if no per-source rule already renamed it). Wildcards: keys under '*' apply to every source. Matching order: per-source rules first (can rename, chain continues), then '*' rules.",

  "_organization": "Rules under '*' are organized by purpose: (1) Brand consolidation; (2) Abbreviation-pair canonicalization; (2b) Country-name consolidation; (3) Fraunhofer cluster (parent vs institutes); (4) Universal legal-suffix stripping; (5) Common-noun drops; (5b) Domain/URL fragments; (5c) Cryptographic placeholder names (Alice/Bob/Eve/...); (5d) Web scraper noise (Cookiebot/GitHub/social media); (5e) Journals and publication venues; (6) Context-dependent drops.",

  "_review_notes": [
    "SQC is BOTH 'Silicon Quantum Computing' (Aus) and 'Swiss Quantum Commission' -- kept separate intentionally.",
    "SAS is BOTH 'Slovak Academy of Sciences' and 'SAS Institute' software firm, plus French legal suffix -- kept separate.",
    "ISTA: 'Israel Institute of Technology (ISTA)' looks like a misextraction (Technion is the usual abbreviation; ISTA normally = Institute of Science and Technology Austria). Spot-check the source.",
    "Honeywell Quantum Solutions was historically a distinct org that merged with Cambridge Quantum to form Quantinuum -- kept separate from 'Honeywell'.",
    "Microsoft Quantum and IBM Quantum are research orgs and are deliberately KEPT SEPARATE from their parent brands.",
    "Google DeepMind is a research org distinct from Google -- kept separate.",
    "Alice / Bob / Eve / etc. are cryptographic placeholder names. The COMPANY 'Alice-Bob' (alice-bob.com) is preserved -- drop rules use ^...$ anchors.",
    "DTU Fotonik is a specific institute within DTU and is KEPT SEPARATE from DTU itself, same logic as Fraunhofer institutes vs Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft.",
    "Bundeswehr University Munich is a different university from TUM -- kept separate.",
    "Web-scraper noise (Cookiebot, WordPress, Webflow, HubSpot, GitHub, GitLab, OpenVPN, Vimeo, YouTube, LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, X) is dropped unconditionally. These are extraction artifacts from page footers/script tags, not real actors. TRADEOFF: GitHub/GitLab as code-host companies are real orgs in some contexts; if you ever need them, remove the specific rule.",
    "Journals (arXiv, Nature, Science, Physical Review Letters, Physical Review X, PRX Quantum, IEEE, SPIE, Nature Communications, Nature Nanotechnology) are dropped. They are publication venues, not actors. TRADEOFF: IEEE is also a real standards body; if your analysis covers standards, remove the IEEE rule.",
    "Famous physicists (Albert Einstein, Max Planck, Peter Shor, David Wineland) are NOT dropped -- they exist as actors but may need person-vs-org treatment in future analysis."
  ],

  "rewrites": {

    "Japan25.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "Japan" },
      { "match": "^our country$",                   "replace": "Japan" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "Japan Government" },
      { "match": "^(the )?national government$",    "replace": "Japan Government" }
    ],

    "China25.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "China" },
      { "match": "^(the )?state council$",          "replace": "China State Council" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "China Government" },
      { "match": "^(the )?national government$",    "replace": "China Government" }
    ],

    "Canada25.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "Canada" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "Canada Government" },
      { "match": "^(the )?federal government$",     "replace": "Canada Government" }
    ],

    "India25.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "India" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "India Government" }
    ],

    "Germany25.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "Germany" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "Germany Government" },
      { "match": "^(the )?federal government$",     "replace": "Germany Government" },
      { "match": "^(the )?bundesregierung$",        "replace": "Germany Government" }
    ],

    "France23.pdf": [
      { "match": "^we$",                            "replace": "France" },
      { "match": "^(the )?government$",             "replace": "France Government" }
    ],

    "FrancoGerman25.pdf": [
